13: // LockDisabled implements State and Locker but disables state locking.
14: // If State doesn't support locking, this is a no-op. This is useful for
15: // easily disabling locking of an existing state or for tests.
16: type LockDisabled struct {
17: 	// We can't embed State directly since Go dislikes that a field is
18: 	// State and State interface has a method State
19: 	Inner Full
